I give them 4 stars for the food, but 1 star for customer service and prices! The food is really good, I've had everything from chicken, pernil, sancocho, soup, steak. The lemonade is also good. Now to the customer service.. They have horrible customer service. We stopped going here because the ladies would ignore us even though we were standing right in front of them wanting to order. This happened almost every single time we would go.  On top of the horrible customer service, their prices are ridiculous. They charge $8+ for a small lunch with chicken when restaurants in the neighborhood charge as little as $6 for the same meal. On top of the price they also charge tax, so you're basically paying almost $10 for a small chicken lunch. The entrees are over priced as well. For any entree they want $15-$22 to serve it with rice and beans, that's just ridiculous. I have never paid that price for that kind of meal. They really price their meals as if they are an upscale restaurant,  but they are far from it.
